<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 07 at 4:13AM EDT  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...Thunderstorms with heavy rainfall affecting Lapeer, Shiawassee
and Genesee Counties...
At 410 AM EDT, Doppler radar indicated thunderstorms with heavy
rainfall along a line extending from Clifford to near Byron,
including the Flint metro area. Movement was northeast at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Heavy rainfall.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Heavy rainfall will reduce visibility for motorists and
could lead to ponding of water on area roads.
Locations impacted include...
Flint, Fenton, Lapeer, Flushing, Grand Blanc, Davison, Imlay City,
Durand, Almont, Clio, Perry, North Branch, Columbiaville, Burton,
Swartz Creek, Hadley, Linden, Mount Morris, Goodrich and Dryden.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>Heavy rainfall may lead to localized flooding. Do not drive your
vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
